# Project Skills Guidance

When discussing, designing, or implementing this project, first consider the installed project skills under `.agents/skills/` and third-party skill references under `.agents/third-party-skills/`.

Default behavior:

- Use `diagnose` style thinking for bugs, failures, flaky execution, Appium issues, WebSocket issues, AI/Phoenix evaluation failures, and unclear root causes.
- Use `tdd` style thinking for risky backend, runner, evaluator, report, RAG, and workflow changes: prefer small verifiable slices and clear regression checks.
- Use `grill-with-docs` / `grill-me` style thinking when requirements are ambiguous, broad, or likely to affect platform information architecture.
- Use `to-prd` / `to-issues` style thinking when turning `docs/product/AIжµ‹иЇ•е№іеЏ°PRD.md` or design discussions into implementation tasks.
- Use `improve-codebase-architecture` / `zoom-out` style thinking when changes affect shared models, services, execution flow, RAG, Skills, Prompt, Evaluator, or report architecture.
- Use `product-on-purpose/pm-skills` as product management guidance for personas, problem statements, JTBD, opportunity trees, OKRs, acceptance criteria, dashboards, and iteration decisions.
- Use `github/awesome-copilot` PRD / Product Manager Advisor references for PRD structure, measurable success criteria, user stories, non-goals, AI evaluation strategy, and issue quality.

